                        <bindingDesc>
                            <binding contemporary="true Ethiopian">
                                <decoNote xml:id="b1" type="bindingMaterial">
                                  <term key="quarterCover">Quarter cover</term>. The book is bound in <material key="wood">wooden</material> boards partially covered with reddish-brown <material key="leather">leather</material>.
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="Boards">
                                  The boards are flush the bookblock and have external shallow bevels. The grain runs vertically.
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote xml:id="b3" type="Cover" color="reddish-brown">
                                  The boards and the spine are partially covered with plain leather.
                                  The upper board is almost entirely covered, while only half of the lower board is. The turn-ins are not well adhered and are partially detached from the boards.
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote xml:id="b4" type="Endbands" color="brown">
                                  Brown <term key="slitBraid">slit-braid</term> endbands are present.
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote xml:id="b5" type="SewingStations">4</decoNote>
                                <decoNote xml:id="b6">
                                  Chainstitch sewing on four sewing stations (two pairs); periodic fold pattern. Two Z-plied threads are used.
                                  The sewing starts from the first quire where, for each pair of sewing stations, there is one length of thread,
                                  while in the rest of the quires there are two. The threads are knotted in the last quire.
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote xml:id="b7" type="Spine">
                                  Horizontal short stitches pierce the leather on the spine in two points (at the head and tail), thus fixing the endbands to the cover.
                                </decoNote>
                            </binding>
                        </bindingDesc>

